example.solution:
We use the properties of exponents, and demonstrate the simplification one step per-line
\begin{aligned}[t] f(t) & = 2\left(3^t\right)\left(3^{3t}\right) & \\ & = 2\left(3^{t+3t}\right) & \text{\ref{exp-prop-add}} \\ & = 2\left(3^{4t}\right) & \\ & = 2(3^4)^t & \text{\ref{exp-prop-mult}} \\ & = 2(81)^t & \end{aligned}
\begin{aligned}[t] g(t) & = 7(1.08)^t(3.2)^t & \\ & = 7(1.08\cdot3.2)^t & \text{\ref{exp-prop-pow}} \\ & = 7(3.456)^t & \end{aligned}
\begin{aligned}[t] h(t) & = 8^t\left(2^{\frac{t+1}{2}}\right) & \\ & = (2^3)^t\left(2^{\frac{t+1}{2}}\right) & \\ & = 2^{3t}\left(2^{\frac{t+1}{2}}\right) & \\ & = 2^{3t+\frac{t+1}{2}} & \text{\ref{exp-prop-add}} \\ & = 2^{\frac{7t+1}{2}} & \\ & = \left(2^{\sfrac{1}{2}}\right)^{7t+1} & \text{\ref{exp-prop-pow}} \\ & = \left(\sqrt{2}\right)\left(\sqrt{2}\right)^{7t} & \text{\ref{exp-prop-add}} \\ & = \left(\sqrt{2}\right)\left(\left(\sqrt{2}\right)^{7}\right)^t & \text{\ref{exp-prop-pow}} \\ & = \left(\sqrt{2}\right)\left(\sqrt{128}\right)^t \end{aligned}

